\name{RAI_fun}
\alias{RAI_fun}
%- Also NEED an '\alias' for EACH other topic documented here.
\title{
Relative Abundance Index
}
\description{
the function returns RAI (i.e., relative abundance index)
}
\usage{
RAI_fun(data, bygrid = FALSE, by_year = FALSE, method = "RAI_2")
}
%- maybe also 'usage' for other objects documented here.
\arguments{
  \item{data}{
 a data frame
}
  \item{bygrid}{
TRUE or FALSE. default by FALSE.
}
  \item{by_year}{
TRUE or FALSE. default by FALSE.
}
  \item{method}{
  there are three main methods:
  RAI_1: Carbone et al, 2001
  RAI_2: Kawanishi et al, 1999
  RAI_3: Wu et al, 2012
  default by RAI_2.
}
}
\details{
%%  ~~ If necessary, more details than the description above ~~
}
\value{
relative abundance index
%%  If it is a LIST, use
%%  \item{comp1 }{Description of 'comp1'}
%%  \item{comp2 }{Description of 'comp2'}
%% ...
}
\references{

Kawanishi K, Sahak AM, Sunquist M ( 1999) Preliminaty analysis on abundance of large mammals at Sungai Relau, Taman Negara The Journal of Wildlife and Parks, 17, 62-82.

Carbone C, Christie S, Conforti K, Coulson T, Franklin N, Ginsberg JR, Griffiths M, Holden J, Kinnaird M, Laidlaw R, Lynam A, MacDonald DW, Martyr D, McDougal C, Nath L, Oâ€™Brien T, Seidensticker J, Smith JLD, Tilson R, Shahruddin WNW ( 2002) The use of photographic rates to estimate densities of cryptic mammals: Response to Jennelle et al Animal Conservation, 5, 121-123.

Wu PF, Liu XH, Cai Q, He XB, Songer M, Zhu Y, Shao XM ( 2012) The application of infrared camera in mammal research in Guanyinshan Nature Reserve, Shaanxi Acta Theriologica Sinica, 32, 67-71. (in Chinese with English abstract)

}
\author{
Hai-Dong Li
}
\note{
%%  ~~further notes~~
}

